Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:26.819 --> 03:31.819
Sync and corrections for www.addic7ed.com

03:31.953 --> 03:39.953
Bitten 2x08 - Dark Arts
03/28/2015

03:43.863 --> 03:49.110
( ♪ )

03:57.521 --> 03:59.121
Jeremy: (distant) Clay!

04:08.531 --> 04:11.032
Jeremy: Clay!

04:11.034 --> 04:12.300
(Groaning)

04:20.476 --> 04:22.377
Clay!

04:22.379 --> 04:23.944
Where have you been?

04:23.946 --> 04:25.279
Been looking all over for you.

04:25.281 --> 04:27.748
I was attacked.

04:27.750 --> 04:29.216
By Eduardo?

04:29.218 --> 04:31.652
Yeah. He set a trap.

04:31.654 --> 04:34.121
You okay?

04:34.123 --> 04:35.723
I just came to.

04:35.725 --> 04:38.292
Don't worry, we'll hit
him back twice as hard, okay?

04:38.294 --> 04:40.027
I'm sorry, Jeremy.

04:40.029 --> 04:42.028
Maybe we can still find him.

04:42.030 --> 04:44.798
He's probably halfway
back to Spain by now.

04:44.800 --> 04:46.700
Let's get you back to Stonehaven

04:46.702 --> 04:48.569
and I'll take a look at that.

04:48.571 --> 04:51.271
Roman will want to know that
Eduardo's still on the loose.

04:51.273 --> 04:52.573
Call him.

04:54.409 --> 04:56.943
(Ominous music)

04:56.945 --> 05:01.945
( ♪ )

05:05.053 --> 05:06.352
(Regular breathing)

05:23.036 --> 05:24.270
What happened?

05:24.272 --> 05:25.938
Did Savannah do this too?

05:25.940 --> 05:28.040
Savannah had nothing to do with that.

05:28.042 --> 05:30.843
She bled a man out, yesterday.

05:30.845 --> 05:33.946
There's no telling what she'll do next.

05:33.948 --> 05:36.615
We'll be gone soon. But
you just got here.

05:36.617 --> 05:39.151
We need to bring Savannah home
for her Initiation ritual.

05:39.153 --> 05:42.121
She needs her talisman
to focus her powers.

05:42.123 --> 05:43.922
So that something
terrible like last night

05:43.924 --> 05:45.157
doesn't happen again.

05:45.159 --> 05:47.024
Why go all the way back to Boston?

05:47.026 --> 05:48.460
Do your ritual here.

05:50.896 --> 05:52.497
No. No, no, no.

05:52.499 --> 05:53.765
We've imposed enough.

05:53.767 --> 05:55.066
Well if she is dangerous,

05:55.068 --> 05:57.101
you should do it as soon as possible.

05:57.103 --> 05:58.436
He's right.

05:58.438 --> 06:00.972
We shouldn't take the chance.

06:00.974 --> 06:03.741
How quickly can it be done?

06:03.743 --> 06:05.376
We should be out by night fall.

06:05.378 --> 06:09.247
( ♪ )

06:09.249 --> 06:10.748
(Rattle)

06:13.518 --> 06:14.852
(Distant metallic banging)

06:19.258 --> 06:20.524
(Banging)

06:23.762 --> 06:25.028
(Banging)

06:27.832 --> 06:29.099
(Banging)

06:36.174 --> 06:38.275
(Echoing) Elena?

06:38.277 --> 06:39.542
Jeremy?

06:39.544 --> 06:40.877
(Banging continues)

06:44.816 --> 06:46.082
(Banging)

06:47.484 --> 06:49.019
(Rattle of doorknob)

06:49.021 --> 06:51.688
Aleister: You werewolves
are full of surprises.

06:51.690 --> 06:53.189
Clay: What are you doing here?

06:53.191 --> 06:55.991
I could ask you the same thing.

06:55.993 --> 06:57.259
(Yelling)

06:58.462 --> 07:01.831
Aleister: Do you even
know where "here" is?

07:01.833 --> 07:03.165
Stonehaven.

07:03.167 --> 07:04.834
Stonehaven of sorts.

07:04.836 --> 07:07.403
The one inside your mind,
your subconscious.

07:07.405 --> 07:10.505
(Banging)
A great woman taught me this spell.

07:10.507 --> 07:13.943
I've taken possession of your body.

07:13.945 --> 07:15.211
Out there, in the real world,

07:15.213 --> 07:17.479
they think I'm you.

07:17.481 --> 07:18.680
No, I'm right here.

07:18.682 --> 07:21.416
You see, that is what's surprising.

07:21.418 --> 07:23.552
Your consciousness
should already be dead.

07:23.554 --> 07:25.920
Gone from here.

07:25.922 --> 07:27.556
You are quite the fighter.

07:27.558 --> 07:30.692
You haven't even begun to see me fight!

07:30.694 --> 07:32.461
You don't have any
control over your body.

07:32.463 --> 07:36.398
I do. I have you locked
away inside your mind.

07:36.400 --> 07:38.032
There is no way out.

07:38.034 --> 07:40.168
Oh, no, no, Elena will
know you're not me.

07:40.170 --> 07:41.770
By the time I'm done with your body,

07:41.772 --> 07:44.072
I'll have broken that bitch's heart.

07:44.074 --> 07:46.107
Not before she rips out yours.

07:46.109 --> 07:47.675
You mean <i>yours.</i>

07:47.677 --> 07:49.310
It's your body.

07:49.312 --> 07:52.113
I only need it until I get back to mine.

07:52.115 --> 07:53.348
(Banging)

07:53.350 --> 07:54.615
And you'll be dead.

07:54.617 --> 07:57.051
Once Savannah has her talisman,

07:57.053 --> 07:58.786
I'll take her.

07:58.788 --> 08:01.555
We have some unfinished business.

08:01.557 --> 08:03.223
(Growling)

08:03.225 --> 08:04.492
(Grunting)

08:05.927 --> 08:07.194
(Banging)

08:15.270 --> 08:16.536
(Banging)

08:17.638 --> 08:19.006
Elena: You ready to go, Savannah?

08:19.008 --> 08:20.307
You almost packed?

08:20.309 --> 08:21.541
Elena?

08:25.313 --> 08:28.515
Ruth is pretty upset, huh?

08:28.517 --> 08:29.849
And you?

08:31.919 --> 08:34.053
I didn't kill that man.

08:34.054 --> 08:37.657
Or if I did, I... I didn't mean to.

08:37.659 --> 08:38.825
Savannah.

08:38.827 --> 08:41.159
It's okay, I'm not judging you.

08:41.162 --> 08:42.462
Of course.

08:45.966 --> 08:48.067
You pack light.

08:48.069 --> 08:50.836
Story of my life.

08:50.838 --> 08:53.306
What does that mean?

08:53.308 --> 08:55.874
I have this Altar Vessel at home

08:55.876 --> 08:58.311
and I'm just supposed
to fill it with stuff.

08:58.313 --> 08:59.979
Things that will...

08:59.981 --> 09:03.882
you know, give me courage
during the Initiation. And...

09:03.884 --> 09:05.984
So far it's pretty empty.

09:11.357 --> 09:13.325
Before all of this craziness,

09:13.327 --> 09:15.360
I was a photographer.

09:17.263 --> 09:18.497
Take this.

09:18.499 --> 09:20.265
It's one of my favorites.

09:20.267 --> 09:23.134
A reminder that we're more
than just wolves and witches.

09:23.136 --> 09:25.036
It's beautiful.

09:27.539 --> 09:29.307
Thank you.

09:29.309 --> 09:31.109
You're welcome.
(Door opens)

09:32.544 --> 09:35.113
Elena: You're back. I
was getting worried.

09:37.983 --> 09:39.283
Clay, you're hurt!

09:39.285 --> 09:40.485
I'm fine.

09:40.487 --> 09:42.252
You should come downstairs.

09:42.254 --> 09:43.955
Ruth has some good news.

09:46.124 --> 09:51.124
( ♪ )

10:01.207 --> 10:02.739
(In foreign language)

10:04.376 --> 10:08.245
(Mixed eerie whispers)

10:08.247 --> 10:11.747
( ♪ )

10:15.654 --> 10:17.654
(In foreign language)

10:24.762 --> 10:26.195
With this anointment,

10:26.197 --> 10:28.864
the Initiation begins.

10:28.866 --> 10:31.467
We call upon all those on the nexus

10:31.469 --> 10:34.270
and we humbly request their powers

10:34.272 --> 10:36.605
as we initiate Savannah Levine.

10:38.808 --> 10:40.343
Go ahead.

10:51.521 --> 10:54.322
(Roar of fire)

10:54.324 --> 10:55.758
You initiate through fire

10:55.760 --> 10:57.927
as your catalytic element.

10:57.929 --> 10:59.461
(Nervous sigh)

11:07.703 --> 11:10.672
(Muffled scratching and squeaks)

11:10.674 --> 11:12.107
Oh my God, they're in the walls.

11:12.109 --> 11:13.375
They're not in the walls.

11:13.377 --> 11:15.444
It's just an echo of the card.

11:15.446 --> 11:16.678
It's fine, Savannah.

11:16.680 --> 11:18.245
You've chosen a great familiar.

11:18.247 --> 11:21.049
Paige, I am <i>terrified</i> of rats.

11:21.051 --> 11:24.251
They are clever, alert, intuitive...

11:24.253 --> 11:25.853
I'm just going to chose another card.

11:25.855 --> 11:27.188
No, Savannah...

11:27.190 --> 11:29.123
It's been chosen.

11:32.728 --> 11:34.328
I want to have Elena with me.

11:34.330 --> 11:36.097
No.

11:36.099 --> 11:38.932
The Initiation only works if
you meet your familiar alone.

11:38.934 --> 11:41.235
But for the first part,
can she be with me then?

11:41.237 --> 11:42.436
Savannah...

11:42.438 --> 11:44.972
She can be with you at the first part.

11:44.974 --> 11:48.275
But when you go in,
you must do it alone.

11:48.277 --> 11:49.843
Do you understand?

11:52.847 --> 11:54.280
She needs an Altar Vessel with her

11:54.282 --> 11:57.017
when she's alone on her ritual.

11:57.019 --> 11:58.919
Poor kid has nothing here.

11:58.921 --> 12:01.655
Why do you want any part in this ritual?

12:01.657 --> 12:03.824
If it helps, what harm can it do?

12:05.660 --> 12:07.427
Can I borrow this?

12:07.429 --> 12:08.928
No.

12:09.863 --> 12:13.166
I... It's too fragile.

12:13.168 --> 12:15.568
Shouldn't be out in the woods.

12:15.570 --> 12:17.537
You must have something.

12:21.542 --> 12:23.109
Survey maps?

12:24.477 --> 12:26.578
You building us a little cottage?

12:28.915 --> 12:31.383
Right now, I'm more worried about you.

12:33.820 --> 12:35.354
Savannah is a dangerous kid.

12:35.356 --> 12:36.689
Until she has her talisman,

12:36.691 --> 12:38.223
you should steer clear.

12:38.225 --> 12:41.160
She means a lot to me, you know that.

12:41.162 --> 12:43.195
Of course.

12:43.197 --> 12:45.730
(Ominous music)

12:45.732 --> 12:50.732
( ♪ )

12:59.312 --> 13:02.213
I'm going to go look for
a vessel for Savannah.

13:02.215 --> 13:04.949
I'm sure Jeremy has something.

13:08.253 --> 13:13.253
( ♪ )

13:18.097 --> 13:21.732
Hey. Can I help?

13:21.734 --> 13:23.334
Need a match?

13:23.336 --> 13:26.036
A match isn't the right
fire for the Initiation.

13:26.038 --> 13:28.406
We need four of the nine sacred woods.

13:28.408 --> 13:30.941
Luckily, they're not that
hard to find around here.

13:30.943 --> 13:32.542
You've got oak,

13:32.544 --> 13:35.278
ash, birch...

13:36.881 --> 13:38.048
...and alder.

13:38.050 --> 13:41.018
Ah. Alder, of course. Yes.

13:41.020 --> 13:42.686
You know, wolves have rituals too.

13:48.426 --> 13:51.461
- I can't seem to stay away from you.
- Mmmm...

13:51.463 --> 13:52.829
(Light blowing)

13:52.831 --> 13:54.831
Nick: I miss the feel of you.

13:54.833 --> 13:58.333
( ♪ )

14:02.140 --> 14:04.006
We don't have time for this.

14:04.008 --> 14:06.475
So then let's steal the time.

14:06.477 --> 14:11.477
( ♪ )

14:22.692 --> 14:24.893
This is the last time.

14:27.530 --> 14:29.531
Whatever you say.

14:29.533 --> 14:34.533
( ♪ )

14:45.381 --> 14:47.916
(Gasping, moaning)

14:51.087 --> 14:56.087
( ♪ )

15:17.078 --> 15:20.578
( ♪ )

15:23.686 --> 15:26.286
(Heavy breathing)

15:39.767 --> 15:41.367
Ruth: I know it seems strange,

15:41.369 --> 15:43.489
but this component of the
ritual has to be done alone.

15:45.139 --> 15:47.907
Whatever it takes, I'm here to help.

15:47.909 --> 15:49.876
Nick: Why are you building
this all the way out here?

15:49.878 --> 15:53.079
Jeremy wanted it in the back
field, closer to the house.

15:53.081 --> 15:54.480
If they need solitude,

15:54.482 --> 15:55.949
I thought this is where they'll find it.

15:55.951 --> 15:57.250
Well, Jeremy won't like it.

15:57.252 --> 15:58.718
We have to rebuild this
in the right place.

15:58.720 --> 16:00.219
This is the right place.

16:00.221 --> 16:01.721
We don't want to cause trouble.

16:03.990 --> 16:05.758
It's no trouble,
I'll just move it for you.

16:05.760 --> 16:07.059
Leave it.

16:08.995 --> 16:12.164
Hmm, somebody's been dipping their wick.

16:12.166 --> 16:13.766
What the hell does that mean?

16:13.768 --> 16:16.801
She's nothing but a little witch whore.

16:16.803 --> 16:18.503
You're out of line right now.

16:18.505 --> 16:20.005
Apologize to her.

16:20.007 --> 16:21.206
(Grunting)

16:21.208 --> 16:23.342
What are you doing?

16:23.344 --> 16:24.743
Kicking your ass.

16:26.545 --> 16:29.114
(Fighting grunts)

16:31.484 --> 16:33.451
Oh, stop it!

16:33.453 --> 16:36.654
(Groans, grunts)

16:36.656 --> 16:37.955
Stop it!

16:37.957 --> 16:39.791
Nick. Nick. Enough. Enough.

16:39.793 --> 16:41.760
Enough!

16:41.762 --> 16:44.295
(Panting)

16:49.784 --> 16:51.051
Elena: Are you crazy?

16:51.053 --> 16:52.619
Fighting Nick?

16:52.621 --> 16:54.221
It's the witches.

16:54.223 --> 16:56.623
They're tearing us apart.
I won't let that happen.

16:56.625 --> 16:58.525
Listen to yourself.

16:58.527 --> 17:00.593
This isn't you.

17:00.595 --> 17:02.128
You're right.

17:02.130 --> 17:04.230
<i>This</i> is me.

17:04.232 --> 17:05.932
Clay, no. Stop.

17:05.934 --> 17:08.501
(Grunting)

17:08.502 --> 17:09.702
What are you...?

17:09.704 --> 17:11.603
Stop it, what's wrong with you?

17:11.605 --> 17:14.839
Both: (Effort grunts)

17:14.842 --> 17:16.075
(Groan)

17:18.278 --> 17:19.877
(Door slam)
Elena!

17:32.792 --> 17:34.092
(Distant banging)

17:35.462 --> 17:36.728
Hello?

17:39.599 --> 17:42.200
(Indistinct, echoing voice)

17:43.436 --> 17:45.971
(Knocking on door)

17:53.279 --> 17:55.447
I count on you to help me
keep this Pack together,

17:55.449 --> 17:57.315
not tear it apart.

17:57.317 --> 17:58.883
What happened between you and Nick?

17:58.885 --> 18:00.218
It was a misunderstanding.

18:00.220 --> 18:01.486
About what?

18:01.488 --> 18:02.687
The witches.

18:02.689 --> 18:04.589
I was wrong about
letting them stay here.

18:04.591 --> 18:06.390
They'll be gone in a few hours.

18:06.392 --> 18:07.558
And then what happens?

18:07.560 --> 18:09.660
We go back to the way things were, Clay.

18:09.662 --> 18:12.897
Elena's feelings for
that girl are a problem.

18:12.899 --> 18:15.199
She wants to protect her.
She's obsessed.

18:15.201 --> 18:18.502
I have faith in Elena's ability
to put the Pack first.

18:20.605 --> 18:23.307
There are things you don't know.

18:23.309 --> 18:24.941
About Elena.

18:24.943 --> 18:28.278
About what happened at the compound.

18:28.280 --> 18:31.548
(Ominous music)

18:31.550 --> 18:33.583
It's a lovely dress. Where'd you get it?

18:33.585 --> 18:35.585
Oh, it was from Paige.

18:35.587 --> 18:38.655
She said I could keep it after.

18:38.657 --> 18:42.692
Ruth and Paige, they...
they care a lot about you.

18:42.694 --> 18:44.694
Savannah, you look great.

18:46.330 --> 18:48.632
Thanks.

18:48.634 --> 18:51.567
Do you, um... do you
guys think I'm ready?

18:51.569 --> 18:52.902
Yeah, I do.

18:52.904 --> 18:54.137
Well, we can't delay.

18:54.139 --> 18:55.471
I'll get my things.

18:57.707 --> 19:00.143
Paige.

19:00.145 --> 19:02.512
Before we go...

19:02.514 --> 19:03.812
I have to ask you...

19:05.749 --> 19:08.884
The way that Savannah can't control
her magic, is that normal?

19:13.322 --> 19:16.025
It's a powerful force.

19:16.027 --> 19:18.193
She's like a grenade
with the pin pulled.

19:18.195 --> 19:20.295
You throw it in the right
direction, everything's okay.

19:20.297 --> 19:21.430
And if not...

19:21.432 --> 19:23.365
But how out-of-control can it get?

19:25.101 --> 19:27.235
Can it affect other people?

19:28.771 --> 19:30.572
Why? What's going on?

19:32.308 --> 19:34.276
Clay: At the compound, she was...

19:34.278 --> 19:36.111
forced to Change.

19:36.113 --> 19:39.614
In front of people.
It's really thrown her.

19:39.616 --> 19:41.583
That's an incredible violation.

19:43.852 --> 19:45.887
But she never has to see
those people again.

19:45.889 --> 19:48.089
And they will not remember seeing her.

19:48.091 --> 19:49.857
One will.

19:49.859 --> 19:51.258
One of them was Rachel.

19:53.428 --> 19:55.597
Elena never told me that.

19:55.599 --> 19:57.030
She didn't?

20:02.437 --> 20:06.574
Why would she keep it a secret
if it wasn't troubling her?

20:06.576 --> 20:09.676
I think this relationship
with Savannah, she's...

20:09.678 --> 20:12.246
she's trying to find
the good in what happened.

20:15.349 --> 20:18.551
And you're worried that the more
time she spends with this girl...

20:20.387 --> 20:23.556
the harder it will be for her to
deal with what's really wrong.

20:23.558 --> 20:25.692
The ceremony only deepens their bond.

20:28.029 --> 20:30.563
It's your decision, Jeremy.
I only thought you should know.

20:33.400 --> 20:34.734
I'll deal with it.

20:38.071 --> 20:39.305
Thank you.

20:47.614 --> 20:48.981
(Door closing)

20:48.983 --> 20:52.483
( ♪ )

20:55.690 --> 20:58.457
Elena: There's something
different about Clay.

20:58.459 --> 21:00.793
He's angry. Aggressive with me.

21:00.795 --> 21:02.327
It's like he's someone else.

21:06.666 --> 21:09.601
Aleister messed with
my mind in the compound.

21:09.603 --> 21:11.136
Maybe he taught that to Savannah.

21:11.138 --> 21:14.206
And you think that Savannah
has something to do with it?

21:14.208 --> 21:17.142
That Clay's under some type of spell?

21:17.144 --> 21:19.410
No, it's different
than what happened to me.

21:21.647 --> 21:25.483
It's like... he's not himself.

21:25.485 --> 21:27.618
Look, I get it.

21:27.620 --> 21:29.821
You realize that magic exists,

21:29.823 --> 21:31.056
and that spells can be real,

21:31.058 --> 21:32.256
and when something weird happens,

21:32.258 --> 21:34.625
you think that that's the reason.

21:34.627 --> 21:37.195
But most often there's
a simple explanation.

21:38.897 --> 21:42.132
He loves you, Elena.

21:42.134 --> 21:43.901
And if there's something
wrong with Clay,

21:43.903 --> 21:46.436
you should talk to Clay.

21:46.438 --> 21:48.338
Not me.

21:48.340 --> 21:53.813
( ♪ )

22:00.937 --> 22:05.951
( ♪ )

23:00.528 --> 23:05.673
( ♪ )

23:21.680 --> 23:23.747
(Indistinct echoing voice)

23:25.284 --> 23:27.785
Malcolm: (Echoing)
You're right here, Clayton.

23:31.289 --> 23:33.023
You're dead.

23:33.025 --> 23:35.459
We burned your body.

23:35.461 --> 23:38.428
Yet here I am, Clayton.

23:38.430 --> 23:39.897
Can't get rid of me that easy.

23:39.899 --> 23:43.100
(Metal clanging in distance)

23:43.102 --> 23:44.869
(Panting)

23:44.871 --> 23:46.370
(Grunts of effort)
(Door rattling)

23:46.372 --> 23:48.071
Young Clay: It's no use.
(Frustrated growl)

23:48.073 --> 23:49.806
We're trapped here.

23:51.876 --> 23:53.143
You're not here.

23:53.145 --> 23:54.711
This is not real.

23:54.713 --> 23:57.714
I still live in you,
just like the boy does.

23:57.716 --> 23:58.982
Argh!

24:00.651 --> 24:01.918
Stop.

24:02.953 --> 24:05.121
You can't fight strong anymore.

24:05.123 --> 24:07.624
You want a way out of here, fight smart.

24:09.593 --> 24:11.928
All these years of
teaching you how to battle;

24:11.930 --> 24:13.863
we're back to square one, boy.

24:13.865 --> 24:16.566
He's taken control of my body,

24:16.568 --> 24:18.667
trapped my mind.

24:18.669 --> 24:20.336
I need a way out.

24:20.338 --> 24:22.171
Or else we'll die.

24:31.348 --> 24:32.548
(Shaky breath)

24:32.550 --> 24:34.816
Elena, we need to talk.

24:34.818 --> 24:37.719
Look, Jeremy, I-I didn't
know how to bring it up,

24:37.721 --> 24:38.987
but it's Clay.

24:38.989 --> 24:41.723
He's not himself.

24:41.725 --> 24:43.324
And look,

24:43.326 --> 24:46.962
this is the book that Clay
found in Baton Rouge, right?

24:46.964 --> 24:48.764
And this section talks about

24:48.766 --> 24:50.398
how a... a dark witch

24:50.400 --> 24:53.101
can enter someone else's
body and control it.

24:53.103 --> 24:55.903
You think that someone's possessed Clay?

24:59.208 --> 25:01.142
Clay told me what you were forced to do

25:01.144 --> 25:03.711
at the compound. I know.

25:03.713 --> 25:08.248
- What?
- He said that they made you Change

25:08.250 --> 25:11.251
in front of others. In front of Rachel.

25:13.555 --> 25:17.191
I never... I never told Clay about that.

25:17.193 --> 25:18.893
- What do you mean?
- I mean, the only people

25:18.895 --> 25:21.528
who know about my Change at the compound

25:21.530 --> 25:23.263
are me and Rachel...

25:26.901 --> 25:28.435
And Aleister.

25:29.804 --> 25:32.839
Elena, Aleister is dead.

25:32.841 --> 25:34.774
Paige and Nick burned his body

25:34.776 --> 25:38.044
- and buried the ashes.
- No, Jeremy, I am telling you,

25:38.046 --> 25:40.481
that is not the Clay that I know.

25:40.483 --> 25:41.982
Okay?

25:41.984 --> 25:43.750
Where's Clay right now?

25:45.853 --> 25:47.186
I'm not sure.

25:49.023 --> 25:51.691
Where was he this morning
when this all started?

25:51.693 --> 25:53.426
I found him in one of the storage shacks

25:53.428 --> 25:54.761
on the edge of the property.

25:54.763 --> 25:56.562
Which one? Can you show me?

25:56.564 --> 25:57.896
Yes.

26:04.838 --> 26:07.206
We have to do it now.

26:07.208 --> 26:09.875
But Elena said she'd be here.

26:09.877 --> 26:11.544
I'm sure she has her reasons,

26:11.546 --> 26:13.212
but we've already started
the ritual, Savannah,

26:13.214 --> 26:15.313
we can't take any longer.
You can do this.

26:15.315 --> 26:17.249
You don't need anyone.

26:17.251 --> 26:18.817
Just remember what you are

26:18.819 --> 26:20.485
and where you belong.

26:22.321 --> 26:27.321
( ♪ )

26:30.397 --> 26:32.397
(Speaking in foreign language)

26:32.399 --> 26:36.334
(Whoosh of flames, mixed eerie whispers)

26:38.103 --> 26:40.605
(In foreign language)

26:50.549 --> 26:52.383
(Continues in foreign language)

26:52.385 --> 26:54.986
(Hiss of steam, water bubbling)

26:56.221 --> 27:01.221
( ♪ )

27:12.804 --> 27:14.371
Ruth: You've been through so much.

27:14.373 --> 27:16.607
You've been so brave.

27:16.609 --> 27:18.542
You're stronger than you know.

27:27.351 --> 27:29.052
(Shaky breath)

27:35.492 --> 27:38.027
(Panting)

27:42.766 --> 27:45.468
Savannah: (Speaking in foreign language)

27:51.675 --> 27:54.143
(Panting)

27:54.145 --> 27:56.712
(Ominous ♪)

27:56.714 --> 28:01.714
( ♪ )

28:08.692 --> 28:10.325
Jeremy, he's still alive.

28:10.327 --> 28:12.026
You were right.

28:12.028 --> 28:14.730
This must be his magic.

28:14.732 --> 28:17.065
And if he is here and
he's taken over Clay's body,

28:17.067 --> 28:18.833
we know what he wants next.

28:21.471 --> 28:22.738
Savannah!

28:24.907 --> 28:27.441
(Mixed eerie whispers)

28:30.112 --> 28:32.713
(Squeaking, leaves rustling)

28:40.121 --> 28:42.657
(Panting)

28:42.659 --> 28:47.659
( ♪ )

28:51.733 --> 28:53.633
(Nervous panting)

28:57.338 --> 29:00.307
Savannah: (Speaking in foreign language)

29:00.309 --> 29:02.876
(Whooshing of wind)

29:05.913 --> 29:08.481
Both: (Panting)

29:11.218 --> 29:13.787
(Whispers fading)

29:32.306 --> 29:37.443
( ♪ )

29:37.445 --> 29:39.478
Ruth? Paige?

29:41.280 --> 29:42.581
I did it!

29:43.583 --> 29:46.284
(Rustling)

29:46.286 --> 29:49.521
Ruth! Paige! I did it!

29:51.725 --> 29:54.292
(Footsteps approaching)

29:57.696 --> 29:59.430
(Panting)

30:02.603 --> 30:04.904
Both: (Panting)

30:08.476 --> 30:10.720
Ruth: Who would do this?

30:10.722 --> 30:12.755
Aleister. We found his symbol

30:12.757 --> 30:14.357
in a shack on the property.

30:14.359 --> 30:16.392
But he's dead.

30:16.394 --> 30:19.395
We think that Aleister's still alive...

30:19.397 --> 30:22.197
and that he has possessed Clay
to take Savannah.

30:24.801 --> 30:27.636
We have to find Aleister's body.

30:27.638 --> 30:29.772
He's going to try and kill Clay

30:29.774 --> 30:32.508
within a dark circle that
he's drawn on the floor.

30:32.510 --> 30:35.411
If you can kill Clay's
body outside the circle,

30:35.413 --> 30:38.046
it will trap Aleister's spirit

30:38.048 --> 30:39.381
and he'll die.

30:39.383 --> 30:44.052
H... h... how do we kill the
body and not hurt Clay?

30:44.054 --> 30:45.220
You can't.

30:45.222 --> 30:47.789
Ruth, there has to be a way.

30:47.791 --> 30:49.491
Believe me,

30:49.493 --> 30:50.725
if there was another way,

30:50.727 --> 30:52.427
we would be doing it.

30:52.429 --> 30:55.329
This is a very, very dark magic.

30:55.331 --> 30:58.833
There's no coming back from it.

30:58.835 --> 31:02.570
Possession spells are always
fatal to those possessed.

31:05.007 --> 31:07.074
I'm so sorry.

31:07.076 --> 31:09.443
I am not giving up on Clay!

31:09.445 --> 31:12.213
Listen to me, Jeremy.

31:12.215 --> 31:16.117
The man you love is already gone.

31:16.119 --> 31:19.186
Clay is already dead.

31:19.188 --> 31:21.222
No one can bring him back.

31:21.224 --> 31:24.691
You're asking me to kill my son, Ruth.

31:24.693 --> 31:27.895
I have no idea the hell you
are about to go through.

31:27.897 --> 31:32.897
( ♪ )

31:46.013 --> 31:47.948
Savannah: Please let me out! Clay!

31:47.950 --> 31:49.282
(Trunk slams shut)

31:51.919 --> 31:54.520
(Muffled sobs from trunk)

32:07.901 --> 32:09.635
Jeremy...

32:09.637 --> 32:10.837
what is it?

32:10.839 --> 32:13.105
Where is Clay's truck?

32:13.107 --> 32:14.373
Gone.

32:15.308 --> 32:16.575
I checked his room.

32:16.577 --> 32:17.977
I found these.

32:20.080 --> 32:21.513
Survey maps.

32:21.515 --> 32:22.747
Nick: He cut out this corner.

32:22.749 --> 32:24.549
Looks like he took it with him.

32:24.551 --> 32:27.652
There's an old foundry
right down that road.

32:27.654 --> 32:30.456
That's where he's going
to draw the dark circle.

32:30.458 --> 32:31.756
Elena: Jeremy,

32:31.758 --> 32:34.425
did Ruth tell you how we get Clay back?

32:34.427 --> 32:36.895
We have to find him fast.

32:43.903 --> 32:45.203
(Metallic banging)

32:49.308 --> 32:50.608
(Banging continues)

33:00.585 --> 33:02.387
(Hinges creaking)

33:04.156 --> 33:05.890
(Banging continues)

33:05.892 --> 33:08.759
You're afraid of what you'll find.

33:09.694 --> 33:11.996
(Banging continues)

33:11.998 --> 33:14.498
Clay: Descending stairs

33:14.500 --> 33:17.100
into darkness...

33:17.102 --> 33:18.969
a dream that means death.

33:18.971 --> 33:21.204
It's the only way out.

33:23.107 --> 33:25.075
(Banging)
Don't go.

33:27.211 --> 33:29.712
There's no room for fear.

33:29.714 --> 33:31.581
What's down there,

33:31.583 --> 33:34.084
let it tear down the walls,

33:34.086 --> 33:36.853
let it set you free.

33:36.855 --> 33:39.055
(Banging continues)

33:52.502 --> 33:55.071
(Footfalls echoing)

33:57.807 --> 33:59.007
Ugh!

33:59.009 --> 34:00.742
His scent is here, but it's weak.

34:00.744 --> 34:03.312
We need to split up. How do we stop him?

34:03.314 --> 34:06.282
I don't want either of you
to do what needs to be done.

34:06.284 --> 34:08.417
Find him and I'll finish this.

34:08.418 --> 34:10.119
Hey. Jeremy,

34:10.121 --> 34:12.320
what aren't you telling us?

34:12.322 --> 34:15.090
(Sigh)

34:15.092 --> 34:16.925
You're hiding something from us,

34:16.927 --> 34:19.226
I can see it.

34:19.228 --> 34:23.398
Clay... as we know him, is gone.

34:23.400 --> 34:27.302
- What do you mean?
- The possession spell is fatal.

34:27.304 --> 34:30.638
Ruth made it very clear, it's dark magic.

34:30.639 --> 34:32.773
When Aleister took over his body,

34:32.775 --> 34:34.875
he destroyed Clay's soul.

34:36.411 --> 34:38.980
No. No, I don't believe her.

34:38.982 --> 34:43.050
Jeremy: If there was any other
option, we'd be taking it.

34:43.052 --> 34:46.553
He's gone. And the only way
for us to stop Aleister now

34:46.554 --> 34:50.257
- is to kill Clay.
- Jeremy, that is not going to happen.

34:50.259 --> 34:51.692
What if we find Aleister's body

34:51.694 --> 34:52.960
and just kill it instead?

34:52.962 --> 34:54.762
It's not going to bring Clay back.

34:54.764 --> 34:56.263
That would just lock Aleister

34:56.264 --> 34:58.499
in Clay's body forever.

34:58.501 --> 35:00.167
Then we do that.

35:00.169 --> 35:02.702
We trap him, we hold him in the cage,

35:02.704 --> 35:03.970
and we wait.

35:05.440 --> 35:07.241
Clay's strong, Jeremy,

35:07.243 --> 35:10.076
he can fight this, okay?

35:10.078 --> 35:11.711
I know he can! He will!

35:11.713 --> 35:15.815
It's not going to be Clay in that cage.

35:15.817 --> 35:19.285
And you're going to wait
for the rest of your life,

35:19.287 --> 35:20.920
but he's gone, Elena.

35:22.289 --> 35:24.557
Clay's dead...

35:24.559 --> 35:27.794
and we have to accept that.

35:27.796 --> 35:31.064
We've lost him and I'm sorry.

35:31.066 --> 35:34.066
- Stay here, I will deal with this alone.
Nick: - No.

35:34.068 --> 35:36.169
If Aleister killed my brother,

35:36.171 --> 35:39.038
then he needs to die.

35:39.040 --> 35:41.005
You tell me how.

35:41.007 --> 35:43.241
If you find him, you take him
out of the circle he's in

35:43.243 --> 35:45.377
and you finish him there.

35:45.379 --> 35:47.011
That's what you do.

35:47.013 --> 35:49.914
And that is the only way we
avenge what happened to Clay.

35:56.354 --> 35:58.389
I don't know if I can do this, Nick.

36:00.659 --> 36:03.728
You just stick with me
and you won't have to.

36:04.763 --> 36:06.030
Come on.

36:11.236 --> 36:13.937
Ruth: For those who have come before us,

36:13.939 --> 36:17.575
find and protect our Coven witch.

36:25.450 --> 36:28.151
Paige: What if she's
not with her talisman?

36:28.153 --> 36:31.755
Ruth: We can use the
talisman to find her.

36:31.757 --> 36:33.289
That's it.

36:36.360 --> 36:41.360
( ♪ )

36:53.611 --> 36:54.877
(Grunting)

36:54.879 --> 36:56.178
(Oil drum clattering)

36:59.283 --> 37:01.817
It's over, Aleister.

37:01.819 --> 37:03.385
You took my son.

37:03.387 --> 37:05.221
And now you're going to die.

37:05.223 --> 37:07.223
(Combat grunts)

37:07.225 --> 37:13.200
( ♪ )

37:19.202 --> 37:21.002
One of us will die,

37:21.004 --> 37:22.993
but it won't be me.

37:27.271 --> 37:29.306
(Combat grunts)

37:29.308 --> 37:34.746
( ♪ )

37:36.748 --> 37:39.348
(Pipes clanging)
(Combat grunts)

37:43.921 --> 37:47.189
(Wolf snarling)

37:47.191 --> 37:49.392
(Metal slamming)

37:55.765 --> 37:58.401
(Grunts of combat, pipes clanging)

38:01.738 --> 38:02.905
(Slamming)

38:02.907 --> 38:04.973
(Snarling, growling continues)

38:04.975 --> 38:06.242
(Slamming)

38:13.983 --> 38:16.585
(Combat grunts)

38:16.587 --> 38:21.757
( ♪ )

38:21.759 --> 38:23.725
(Yelling)

38:28.197 --> 38:29.531
(Banging, snarling)

38:33.436 --> 38:38.845
( ♪ )

38:44.847 --> 38:46.180
(Pulley whirring)

38:49.250 --> 38:50.517
Oof!

38:55.096 --> 38:56.964
You're out of your circle now, Aleister.

38:56.966 --> 39:00.000
You'd really do this to your son?

39:00.935 --> 39:03.770
(Vicious snarling)

39:03.772 --> 39:06.105
(Banging)

39:06.107 --> 39:07.407
Jeremy: (Roaring)

39:07.409 --> 39:09.108
(Screaming) Stop!

39:09.110 --> 39:11.778
Ugh!
(Wet impact)

39:11.780 --> 39:13.012
Elena: Oh! Please!

39:13.014 --> 39:14.347
Nick: Let him, let him, let him.

39:14.349 --> 39:15.582
Jeremy, please!

39:15.584 --> 39:17.517
(Grunting, gasping)

39:17.519 --> 39:18.817
(Lock clicking)

39:21.154 --> 39:23.722
(Low, guttural growling)

39:28.528 --> 39:31.931
(Grunting)
Elena: Something's happening.

39:31.933 --> 39:33.199
He's Changing.

39:33.201 --> 39:34.900
I have to kill him, Elena.

39:34.902 --> 39:36.568
Elena: (Shouting) What if it's Clay?

39:36.570 --> 39:39.204
Aleister wasn't able to
control us as wolves.

39:39.206 --> 39:40.906
(Grunting)
What if Clay can Change?

39:40.908 --> 39:42.974
If that is Aleister in Clay's wolf form,

39:42.976 --> 39:44.576
he's going to kill us all, Elena.

39:44.578 --> 39:46.011
Please!

39:46.013 --> 39:48.747
(Grunting in pain)
(Bones cracking)

39:53.152 --> 39:54.886
(Screaming)

39:57.390 --> 39:59.925
(Snarling)

40:06.799 --> 40:08.399
(Roaring)

40:11.603 --> 40:13.638
Elena: Clay?

40:13.640 --> 40:14.906
You're alive.

40:14.908 --> 40:16.206
It's him.

40:17.743 --> 40:18.976
(Sighing)

40:21.346 --> 40:22.613
(Panting)

40:24.950 --> 40:26.350
(Chuckling)

40:26.352 --> 40:29.453
If Clay's alive, does that
mean Aleister is dead?

40:35.560 --> 40:37.094
(Sharp inhalation, panting)

40:38.863 --> 40:41.498
(Muffled sobs, pounding in trunk)

40:48.172 --> 40:51.441
I thought I'd lost you.

40:51.443 --> 40:53.710
I was in there the whole time,

40:53.712 --> 40:55.979
fighting him.
(Grunt of pain)

40:58.182 --> 41:00.850
I could hear you, darling,

41:00.852 --> 41:03.786
but I couldn't find you.

41:03.788 --> 41:06.222
(Grunt)
I'm here now.

41:06.224 --> 41:08.958
And Aleister?

41:08.960 --> 41:10.626
We don't know.

41:10.628 --> 41:14.463
Savannah: (Muffled) Hello?
Hello, can anyone hear me?

41:14.465 --> 41:16.164
Please help me!

41:17.166 --> 41:18.501
You're alive?

41:18.503 --> 41:21.336
So happy I found you.

41:21.338 --> 41:22.638
(Whimpering)

41:26.042 --> 41:27.977
And now that we have this,

41:27.979 --> 41:30.345
you can focus your powers.

41:31.347 --> 41:33.215
You...

41:33.217 --> 41:35.283
you want to kill us all.

41:35.285 --> 41:37.319
I am the lock.

41:37.321 --> 41:40.355
(Mixed eerie whispers)

41:40.357 --> 41:41.656
And I am the key.

41:49.431 --> 41:51.232
(Defeated sigh)

42:00.876 --> 42:02.143
Now...

42:04.946 --> 42:06.213
drink.

42:09.117 --> 42:11.752
(Ominous music)

42:11.754 --> 42:16.754
( ♪ )

42:22.064 --> 42:24.598
(Wind gusting)

42:28.002 --> 42:30.437
(Sonic boom)

42:32.273 --> 42:34.507
Both: (Gasping)

42:34.509 --> 42:36.876
(Eerie shrieking)
Both: (Gasping in pain)

42:42.015 --> 42:43.449
What was that?

42:46.919 --> 42:49.188
Mom... you're bleeding!

42:51.691 --> 42:54.293
What's happening?

42:54.295 --> 42:56.728
It's the beginning of the end.

42:56.730 --> 42:57.730
( ♪ )

